file is displayable image "MAY 2013" WordPress Codex "Function Reference"
=========================================================================

NAME
----

file is displayable image - **file\_is\_displayable\_image** determines whether or not the file

SYNOPSIS
--------

**file\_is\_displayable\_image** determines whether or not the file
passed to it is a displayable JPG, GIF, or PNG image.

USAGE
-----

`  <?php file_is_displayable_image($path); ?> `

EXAMPLES
--------

### Default Usage

    <?php file_is_displayable_image(ABSPATH . "/image/a-picture.jpg"); ?>

PARAMETERS
----------

 `$path` 
:   ([*filesystem
    path*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Filesystem_path "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) The absolute path of the image you want to check.
    Default: *None*

